{"title_page": "Clearing Customs", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name        = Clearing Customs\n| type        = studio\n| artist      = [[Fred Frith]]\n| cover       = FredFrith AlbumCover ClearingCustoms.jpg\n| released    = {{Start date|2011|2}}\n| recorded    = November\u2013December 2007\n| studio      = [[S\u00fcdwestrundfunk|SWR]] studio 1, [[Baden-Baden]] and [[Saarbr\u00fccken]], Germany\n| genre       = {{Flatlist|\n*[[Jazz]]\n*[[free improvisation]]\n}}\n| length      = {{Duration|m=67|s=50}}\n| label       = [[Intakt Records|Intakt]]\n| producer    = \n| prev_title  = [[Eye to Ear III]]\n| prev_year   = 2010\n| next_title  = [[Field Days (The Amanda Loops)]]\n| next_year   = 2015\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1 = [[All About Jazz]]\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=Jones/>\n| noprose = yes\n}}\n{{external media| align=right| width=26p8x| image1=[https://web.archive.org/web/20110726010137/http://walterlayher-fotografie.dyndns.org:8132/v/Konzerte/Tollhaus/Clearing_Customs/?g2_page=1 SWR New Jazz Meeting featuring Fred Frith \u2013 ''Clearing Customs'', November 2007] by Walter Layher}}\n\n'''''Clearing Customs''''' is a studio album by English guitarist, composer and improvisor [[Fred Frith]].<ref name=Intakt/> It is based on a week of recordings and performances in November and December 2007 at a New Jazz Meeting at [[S\u00fcdwestrundfunk|SWR]], a radio station in southwest Germany. Two hour-long national broadcasts were made.<ref name=Mills/> The album was released by [[Intakt Records]] in February 2011.\n\nThe music is based on a 75-minute composition by Frith, and improvised by all the performers.<ref name=Intakt/> It uses a \"graphic structural model\" that links \"diverse types of musical events\" on a time line.<ref name=linernotes/> Traditional jazz instruments were used, plus Asian [[guzheng]] and [[tabla]]s, and electronics. Frith drew on English theatre maker [[Peter Brook]]'s approach of bringing together performers from completely different cultural backgrounds.<ref name=linernotes/>\n\n==Track listing==\nAll tracks composed by [[Fred Frith|Frith]].\n\n#\"Clearing Customs\" \u2013 67:50\n\nSource: [[Discogs]]<ref name=Discogs/>\n\n==Personnel==\n*[[Fred Frith]] \u2013 guitar, home-made instruments\n*[[Wu Fei]] \u2013 [[guzheng]]\n*Anantha Krishnan \u2013 [[mridangam]], [[tabla]]s\n*Marque Gilmore \u2013 drums, electronics\n*Tilman M\u00fcller \u2013 trumpet\n*Patrice Scanlon \u2013 electronics\n*Daniela Cattivelli \u2013 electronics\n\nSource: [[Intakt Records]]<ref name=Intakt/>\n\n===Sound and artwork===\nRecorded at [[S\u00fcdwestrundfunk|SWR]] studio 1 in [[Baden-Baden]], Germany on November 29, 2007, and in [[Saarbr\u00fccken]], Germany on December 1, 2007.\n*Wolfgang Bachner \u2013 recording engineer\n*Alfred Habelitz \u2013 sound engineer\n*[[Fred Frith]] \u2013 mixing, liner notes\n*Manfred Seiler \u2013 mixing\n*Manfred Seiler \u2013 mastering\n*Reinhard Kager \u2013 liner notes\n*Heike Liss \u2013 cover art\n*Jonas Schoder \u2013 graphic design\n\nSource: [[Intakt Records]]<ref name=Intakt/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs=\n\n<ref name=Jones>{{cite web |url=https://www.allaboutjazz.com/clearing-customs-fred-frith-intakt-records-review-by-nic-jones.php |title=Clearing Customs |work=[[All About Jazz]] |first=Nic |last=Jones |accessdate=2015-11-24}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Mills>{{cite web | url = http://www.mills.edu/academics/faculty/mus/frith/frith_cv.php | title = Fred Frith | work = [[Mills College]] | accessdate = 2011-02-21}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Intakt>{{cite web | url = http://www.intaktrec.ch/176-a.htm | title = Clearing Customs | publisher = [[Intakt Records]] | accessdate = 2011-02-21}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Discogs>{{cite web | url = https://www.discogs.com/Fred-Frith-Clearing-Customs/release/2724792 | title = Clearing Customs | work = [[Discogs]] | accessdate = 2011-02-21}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=linernotes>Kager, Reinhard. ''Clearing Customs'' [[liner notes]].</ref>\n\n}}\n\n==External links==\n\n*[http://www.intaktrec.ch/176-a.htm ''Clearing Customs''] at [[Intakt Records]]\n*[http://www.intaktrec.ch/rev176-a.htm ''Clearing Customs'' reviews] at Intakt Records\n\n{{Fred Frith}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Clearing Customs}}\n[[Category:2011 albums]]\n[[Category:Intakt Records albums]]\n[[Category:Fred Frith albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox album\n| name        = Clearing Customs\n| type        = studio\n| artist      = [[Fred Frith]]\n| cover       = FredFrith AlbumCover ClearingCustoms.jpg\n| released    = {{Start date|2011|2}}\n| recorded    = November\u2013December 2007\n| studio      = [[S\u00fcdwestrundfunk|SWR]] studio 1, [[Baden-Baden]] and [[Saarbr\u00fccken]], Germany\n| genre       = {{Flatlist|\n*[[Jazz]]\n*[[free improvisation]]\n}}\n| length      = {{Duration|m=67|s=50}}\n| label       = [[Intakt Records|Intakt]]\n| producer    = \n| prev_title  = [[Eye to Ear III]]\n| prev_year   = 2010\n| next_title  = [[Field Days (The Amanda Loops)]]\n| next_year   = 2015\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1 = [[All About Jazz]]\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref name=Jones/>\n| noprose = yes\n}}\n{{external media| align=right| width=230px| image1=[https://web.archive.org/web/20110726010137/http://walterlayher-fotografie.dyndns.org:8132/v/Konzerte/Tollhaus/Clearing_Customs/?g2_page=1 SWR New Jazz Meeting featuring Fred Frith \u2013 ''Clearing Customs'', November 2007] by Walter Layher}}\n\n'''''Clearing Customs''''' is a studio album by English guitarist, composer and improvisor [[Fred Frith]].<ref name=Intakt/> It is based on a week of recordings and performances in November and December 2007 at a New Jazz Meeting at [[S\u00fcdwestrundfunk|SWR]], a radio station in southwest Germany. Two hour-long national broadcasts were made.<ref name=Mills/> The album was released by [[Intakt Records]] in February 2011.\n\nThe music is based on a 75-minute composition by Frith, and improvised by all the performers.<ref name=Intakt/> It uses a \"graphic structural model\" that links \"diverse types of musical events\" on a time line.<ref name=linernotes/> Traditional jazz instruments were used, plus Asian [[guzheng]] and [[tabla]]s, and electronics. Frith drew on English theatre maker [[Peter Brook]]'s approach of bringing together performers from completely different cultural backgrounds.<ref name=linernotes/>\n\n==Track listing==\nAll tracks composed by [[Fred Frith|Frith]].\n\n#\"Clearing Customs\" \u2013 67:50\n\nSource: [[Discogs]]<ref name=Discogs/>\n\n==Personnel==\n*[[Fred Frith]] \u2013 guitar, home-made instruments\n*[[Wu Fei]] \u2013 [[guzheng]]\n*Anantha Krishnan \u2013 [[mridangam]], [[tabla]]s\n*Marque Gilmore \u2013 drums, electronics\n*Tilman M\u00fcller \u2013 trumpet\n*Patrice Scanlon \u2013 electronics\n*Daniela Cattivelli \u2013 electronics\n\nSource: [[Intakt Records]]<ref name=Intakt/>\n\n===Sound and artwork===\nRecorded at [[S\u00fcdwestrundfunk|SWR]] studio 1 in [[Baden-Baden]], Germany on November 29, 2007, and in [[Saarbr\u00fccken]], Germany on December 1, 2007.\n*Wolfgang Bachner \u2013 recording engineer\n*Alfred Habelitz \u2013 sound engineer\n*[[Fred Frith]] \u2013 mixing, liner notes\n*Manfred Seiler \u2013 mixing\n*Manfred Seiler \u2013 mastering\n*Reinhard Kager \u2013 liner notes\n*Heike Liss \u2013 cover art\n*Jonas Schoder \u2013 graphic design\n\nSource: [[Intakt Records]]<ref name=Intakt/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs=\n\n<ref name=Jones>{{cite web |url=https://www.allaboutjazz.com/clearing-customs-fred-frith-intakt-records-review-by-nic-jones.php |title=Clearing Customs |work=[[All About Jazz]] |first=Nic |last=Jones |accessdate=2015-11-24}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Mills>{{cite web | url = http://www.mills.edu/academics/faculty/mus/frith/frith_cv.php | title = Fred Frith | work = [[Mills College]] | accessdate = 2011-02-21}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Intakt>{{cite web | url = http://www.intaktrec.ch/176-a.htm | title = Clearing Customs | publisher = [[Intakt Records]] | accessdate = 2011-02-21}}</ref>\n\n<r