{"title_page": "The Fight Magazine", "text_new": "{{Infobox magazine\n| title           = The Fight Magazine\n| logo            = \n| logo_size       = \n| category        = Gay magazine\n| frequency       = Monthly\n| format          = Print and Online \n| circulation     = 180,000 Readers\n| founded         = 2011\n| country         = United States\n| based           = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]]\n| language        = English\n| website         = {{URL|http://www.thefightmag.com}}\n}}\n\n'''''The Fight Magazine''''' is [[California]]'s monthly LGBTQ publication, in print and online (www.thefightmag.com). The publication is distributed freely at gay bars, clubs and gay friendly businesses throughout [[California]]. Founded in 2011 the publication covers topics of interest to the LGBTQ community. As of November 2019 the magazine claims a 180,000 monthly readership throughout California. And over 1 million visitors to the Website per month<ref>{{cite web|title=The Fight Magazine|url=http://thefightmag.com|website=http://thefightmag.com|accessdate=17 June 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2014, the actor [[Van Hansis]] (''[[As The World Turns]]'', ''[[Eastsiders]]'') came out in an interview in ''The Fight''.<ref name=\"thefight\">{{cite news| url=http://thefightmag.com/2014/05/turning-point/| accessdate=March 29, 2016 |work=The Fight Magazine |date=May 5, 2014| title=Turning Point |first=Kit |last=Williamson |authorlink=Kit Williamson}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Soap Star Van Hansis Talks About Being Gay In Hollywood & Breaking LGBT Barriers On Daytime TV! Plus, He's Still Yummy! Pics HERE!|url=http://perezhilton.com/tag/van_hansis/|website=perezhilton.com|accessdate=17 June 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Van Hansis on why he didn't come out during ATWT: \"I was completely green \u2026 and honestly, I was scared\"|url=http://greginhollywood.com/van-hansis-on-why-he-didnt-come-out-during-atwt-i-was-completely-green-and-honestly-i-was-scared-99862|website=greginhollywood.com|accessdate=17 June 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=ACTOR VAN HANSIS TALKS ABOUT BEING GAY|url=http://www.towleroad.com/van_hansis/|website=towleroad.com|accessdate=17 June 2014}}</ref>\nAt a launch party for their December 2017 issue at The Abbey in West Hollywood it was announced that the publication will begin producing a San Francisco edition of the magazine in March 2018.\n\n==Company mission==\nThe Fight Magazine advocates for LGBT rights in every aspect of life, be it HIV advancements and management, gay adoption, anti-gay bullying and discrimination to in-depth features on prominent members of the GLBT community in the art world, culture and news.<ref>{{cite web|title=Facebook Info|url=https://www.facebook.com/TheFightMagazine/info|website=https://www.facebook.com|accessdate=17 June 2014}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://thefightmag.com/ Official website]\n*[https://www.facebook.com/TheFightMagazine Facebook]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fight Magazine}}\n[[Category:2011 establishments in California]]\n[[Category:LGBT in California]]\n[[Category:American LGBT-related magazines]]\n[[Category:Magazines established in 2011]]\n[[Category:Magazines published in Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:American monthly magazines]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox magazine\n| title           = The Fight Magazine\n| logo            = \n| logo_size       = \n| category        = Gay magazine\n| frequency       = Monthly\n| format          = Print and Online \n| circulation     = 180,000 Readers\n| founded         = 2011\n| country         = United States\n| based           = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]]\n| language        = English\n| website         = {{URL|http://www.thefightmag.com}}\n}}\n\n'''''The Fight Magazine''''' is [[California]]'s monthly LGBTQ publication, in print and online (www.thefightmag.com). The publication is distributed freely at gay bars, clubs and gay friendly businesses throughout [[California]]. Founded in 2011 the publication cover